old_dat_list <- dat_list

set.seed(1234)
## create initial estimates

#Covariates and placebo
init =  function() list(theta_S0 = rnorm(1,.21,.01), theta_r = rnorm(1,.01,0.001), theta_SEX = rnorm(1,.953,0.01),
                        theta_AGE = rnorm(1,.01,0.001), theta_APOE4_b = rnorm(1,.037,0.01), theta_APOE4_r = rnorm(1,.01,0.001),
                        theta_HV = rnorm(1,.01,0.001), theta_ASFVAL = rnorm(1,.01,0.001),
                        tau = .01, beta = .01, omega_pb = rlnorm(1,log(.405)-.5,1), omega_pr = rlnorm(1,log(.206)-.5),
                        eta_pb = rep(0,dat_list[[2]]), eta_pr = rep(0,dat_list[[2]]))

parametersToPlot <- c("theta_S0","theta_r","theta_SEX","theta_AGE","theta_APOE4_b","theta_APOE4_r", "theta_HV",
                      "theta_ASFVAL", "omega_pb","omega_pr","tau","beta")

 parameters <- c(parametersToPlot)

Run Stan

nChains <- 4

nBurn <-1000 ## Number of burn-in samples per chain after thinning
nThin <- 1

nIter <- (nPost + nBurn) * nThin
nBurnin <- nBurn * nThin

cat(code)  #Prints out code in readible form
## data{
## 
##  int N;                                // number of total Observations
##   int P;                                 // number of subjects
##  int M;                            // number of studies
##      int IDp[N];                           // Patient ID 
##      int IDs[N];                           // Study ID 
##      vector[N] SEX;
##      vector[N] AGE;
##      vector[N] APOE4;
##   vector[N] time;                        // time of observation (years)
##  vector[N] S;                          // measured ADAScog score
##      vector[N] PBLHV;                    // measured Hippocampus Volume
##  //  vector[N] PBLHVLeap;                // measured Hippocampus Volume LEAP
##      vector[N] ASFVAL;                       // measured Affine Scaling Factor
## }
## 
## parameters{
## 
##      //Fixed effects and covariates 
##      real<lower=0,upper=1> theta_S0;         // Mean baseline score for average individual, orig no lower
##      real theta_r;                           // Mean progression rate for average individual, orig no lower
##      real theta_SEX;
##      real theta_AGE;
##      real theta_APOE4_b;
##      real theta_APOE4_r;
##      real theta_HV;
## //       real theta_HVLEAP;
##      real theta_ASFVAL;
##      real tau;            
##      real beta;
## //   real beta_bateman;
## //    real kel;
## //    real keq;
##     
##     
##      //Inter-patient re
##      vector[P] eta_pb;                       // re for patient baseline
##      vector[P] eta_pr;                         // re for patient rate
##  //  vector[M] eta_sb;
## //   vector[M] eta_sr;
##    real<lower=0> omega_pb;                   // std for patient baseline
##    real<lower=0> omega_pr;                   // std for patient rate
##   // real<lower=0> omega_sb;
##   // real<lower=0> omega_sr;
## }
## transformed parameters{
##   
##      vector[N] baseline_cov;
##      vector[N] rate_cov;
##      vector[N] S0;
##      vector[N] r;
##     vector<lower=0,upper=1>[N] muS;
##     real tau_trans;
##     real beta_trans;
##    // real beta_bateman_trans;
##     real keq_trans;
##     real kel_trans;
##     // transform trans to be 
##     tau_trans = (tau+1)*80;
##     beta_trans = (beta +1)*5;
##   //  beta_bateman_trans = exp(beta_bateman-3.5);
##   //  keq_trans = exp(keq+1.88);
##   //  kel_trans = exp(kel+.46);
##     
##     
##   
##      for(i in 1:N) {
## 
##          baseline_cov[i] = theta_S0*(1+theta_SEX*(SEX[i]-1))*(1+theta_APOE4_b*(APOE4[i]-0.72));
##          
##          rate_cov[i] = theta_r*(1+theta_AGE*(AGE[i]-75))*(1+theta_APOE4_r*(APOE4[i]-0.72))*(1+theta_HV*(PBLHV[i]))*(1+theta_ASFVAL*(ASFVAL[i]-0.85));
##         
##         r[i] = rate_cov[i] + eta_pr[IDp[i]];
##         
##          S0[i] = baseline_cov[i]*exp(eta_pb[IDp[i]]);
##          
##          
##          muS[i] = S0[i]/(S0[i]^beta_trans +(1-S0[i]^beta_trans)*exp(-beta_trans*r[i]*time[i]))^(1/beta_trans);
## 
##      }
## }
## model{
## 
##  //Priors
##      omega_pb~cauchy(0,10); 
##      omega_pr~cauchy(0,10);
## //       omega_sb~cauchy(0,10); 
## //       omega_sr~cauchy(0,10); 
##      eta_pb~cauchy(0,omega_pb);
##      eta_pr~cauchy(0,omega_pr);
##  //      eta_sb~normal(0,omega_sb);
##   //     eta_sr~normal(0,omega_sr);
## 
##      theta_S0~cauchy(0,10); 
##      theta_r~cauchy(0,10);
##      theta_SEX~cauchy(0,10);
##      theta_AGE~cauchy(0,10);
##      theta_HV~cauchy(0,10);
##  //      theta_HVLEAP~cauchy(0,10);
##      theta_ASFVAL~cauchy(0,10);
##      theta_APOE4_b~cauchy(0,10);
##       theta_APOE4_r~cauchy(0,10);
##      tau~cauchy(0,10); 
##      beta~cauchy(0,10);
## //       kel~normal(0,1);
## //       keq~normal(0,1);
## //       beta_bateman~normal(0,1);
## 
##       //theta_APOE4_unk~normal(0,1);
##      //theta_APOE4_0~normal(0,1);
##      //theta_APOE4_1~normal(0,1);
##      //theta_APOE4_2~normal(0,1);
##      
##  // Likelihood
##      S ~beta(muS*tau_trans, (1-muS)*tau_trans);
## }
